    • Constructor Detail

      • TrueNTHSignedRequest

        public TrueNTHSignedRequest(java.lang.String signed_request,
                            java.lang.String validationKey)
                     throws java.security.InvalidKeyException,
                            java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException
        Builds a TrueNTHSignedRequest instance from an existing request in a String format.

        To be successfully built, the data must have been signed with validationKey, using a know HMAC algorithm.

        Supported algorithm: "HmacSHA256".

        Signed request data example(assume JSon format): {"issued_at":1445489995,"user_id":10015,"event" :"logout","algorithm":"HMAC-SHA256"}

        Parameters:
        signed_request - Raw string containing the "signed_request": signature+data.
        validationKey - Company's App Secret.
        Throws:
        java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - If the algorithm declared inside the request is not supported.
        java.security.InvalidKeyException - If the key is not suitable for the algorithm.
